3. (1) Subject to the provisions of this regulation, for the purposes of these Defective grain
Regulations, any grain which falls within one or other of the following categories shall be
defective grain:
(a) damaged grain;
(b) discoloured grain;
(c) diseased grain;
(d) germinated grain;
(e) other coloured grain;
(f) s hrivelled grain;
(g) smutty grain;
(h) stained grain;
(i) u ndeveloped grain;
(j) u nthreshed grain.
(2) In the case of unshelled groundnuts, shelled groundnuts shall not be regarded
as defective grain.
